Backgrounds are what your character was doing before they became an adventurer and they all give bonuses related to that task to your character.

Pick from the list below or roll a d100 and leave your character's profession in the hand's of fate (Its more fun this way)

List of Backgrounds:

1-2) Slave: Skill: Athletics Items: Broken Knife, Broken Shackles, 2d4 gold.
3-4) Beggar: Skill: Persuade. Items: Slingshot, Rope, 2d4 Pebbles, 2d4 + 2 gold.
5-6) Thief: Skill: Sleight of Hand. Items: Knife, Rope, 2d4 + 2 gold.
7-8) Cultist: Skill: Lore (Occult). Items: Staff, Ceremonial Robes, 2d4 gold.
9-10) Peasant: Skill: Insight. Items: Sickle, Torch, Improvised Medical Kit, 2d4 + 2 gold.
11-15) Outlaw: Skill: Stealth. Items: Dagger, Lockpicking Tools, 2d4 + 4 gold.
16-20) Mercenary: Skill: Athletics. Items: Longsword, 4d4 + 2 gold.
21-25) Sailor: Skill: . Items: Cutlass, compass, 4d4 + 2 gold. 
26-30) Scout: Skill: Riding. Items: Javelin, Spyglass, 2d4 + 2 gold.
31-35) Performer: Skill: Perform. Items: An Instrument, 2d4 + 4 gold.
36-40) Craftsman: Skill: Craftsmanship Items: Handaxe, Crafting Kit, 4d4 + 4 gold.
41-45) Hunter: Skill: Perceive. Items: Hunting Bow, Trap Kit, 2d4 + 2 gold.
46-50) Student: Skill: Lore (__). Items: Knife, Writing Kit, 4d4 + 2 gold. 
51-55) Astrologer: Skill: Lore (Arcana). Items: Estoc, Sundial, 2d4 + 4 gold.
56-60) Acolyte: Skill: Lore (Religion). Items: Charm, Potion of Moderate Healing, 2d4 + 4 gold.
61-65) Healer: Skill: Medicine. Items: Knife, Medical Kit, 4d4 + 2 gold.
66-70) Alchemist: Skill: Alchemy. Items: Blowgun, Brewing Kit, 2d4 + 2 gold.
71-75) Shepherd: Skill: Animal Handling. Items: Staff, 2d4 gold. A Dog (Familiar).
76-80) Swindler Skill: Deceive. Items: Set of playing cards and die, 2d4 + 4 gold.
81-85) Detective Skill: Investigate. Items: , , 2d4 + 2 gold.
86-90) Soldier: Skill: Intimidate. Items: Spear, 4d4 + 4 gold.
91-92) Outcast: Skill: Frighten. Items: Journal
93-94) Innkeeper: Skill: Persuade. Items: An Improvised Weapon, 2x Bottle of Ale, 4d4 + 4 gold.
